If you are going to #paris #france save this post ☺️
Where to go & what to do PART 1: 

1 The Eiffel Tower, at night & during the way. There is an incredible @bistrotdelatoureiffel right by the Tower where you can try traditional France snails 🐌 dish. And at night we loved to go eat there & watch Eiffel Tower sparkle like a Christmas tree. Just know that there is A LOT of pocket thieves by the tower & in tourist areas so if someone approaches you to tie a bracelet on your wrist or sell you something, hold your wallet tight & do not engage in the conversations.

2 You go on the tour to Eiffel Tower all the way to the top you will see the gorgeous view of Trocadero. Also if you pre book in an advance you can have a dinner inside the Eiffel Tower. They have a restaurant there somewhere in the middle just make sure you prebook in advance!

3 Trocadero district, with a beautiful view of the Eiffel Tower. Beautiful beautiful area.

4 Go to The @louisvuitton headquarters in Paris! Stunning!

5 Catacombs De Paris

6 also my friend @minerva.custom.paris is making incredible custom leather and denim jackets & wallets & other souvenirs to you & your loved once. She is incredibly talented

PART 2 #france #paris & @tarantactical @viktoriia_batarchuk
💖 Save this post & previous if you are planning to visit Paris once day:) I will never forget November 2021💖 Here are second parts of my favorite places to visit in Paris! This city is very special in my heart ❣️ Hope it will be special for you too! 
1) famous the @museelouvre , make sure you have the whole day there & go see The Mona Lisa. And feed the birds 🦅 there are so beautiful there & tons of them

2) @montmartre_in_paris Montmarte district, that’s where 222 steps leading to the Sacré-Coeur, is incredible! Stunning. On top there are very tasty restaurants. My favorite was @aucadetdegascogne And off course Sacre-Coeur is a must at night and during the way. They have a special Love Lock 🔒 there by the church that you can leave with your loved once.

3) Hôtel de Crillon, A Rosewood Hotel is a historic luxury hotel in Paris overlooks the spectacular Place de la Concorde, one of the most beautiful city squares in the world. Has incredible restaurants also with traditional food.

4) The Place de l’Étoile is the largest road junction in Paris and Arc de Triomphe 

5) Tertre and Clichy, where Moulin Rouge is. Highly suggest to go see the show

6) Chateau de Chantilly,France

7) Catacombs De Paris

8) Notre Dame de France

Dear Jon and Tatiana! 

Thank you for the thrilling, warm words addressed to the 127th Separate Brigade of the Territorial Defense of the Armed Forces of UA. It is nice to feel that the talented actors, working in Hollywood, take care about our problems. It seems to be a well-known fact: reality is different from a work of art. But the military-adventure action film "Fury" (2014), where you, John played the role of a participant in the events of the end of the Second World War, makes one feel the real horrors of war. In the film, the hard battles, fear, risk are linked with hope and faith in the future. Today, the right of our people for peaceful life is fought by our military servicemen on the front lines. The war is not over yet, but it will definitely end, and definitely with our victory. And moreover, we are grateful to you, our foreign friend, for the moral support of those who defend Ukraine, in particular in Bakhmut. 

We fight for life, and life always wins!
——————
Шановні @jonnybernthal та @tetianagaidar!
Дякуємо за зворушливі, теплі слова на адресу 127-ї Окремої бригади ТРО ЗСУ. 

Приємно відчувати, що талановиті актори, працюючи в Голівуді, переймаються й нашими проблемами. От ніби то всім відома істина: реальність є відмінною від художнього твору. Та військово-пригодницький бойовик «Лють» (2014 р.) змушує відчувати справжні жахіття війни. 

Ви, Джоне, проживали у ньому роль учасника подій кінця Другої світової війни. У фільмі тяжкі бої, страх, ризик поєднуються з надією і вірою в майбутнє. Подібні ситуації відбуваються й нині на фронті. Та сьогодні право людей на мирне життя виборюють на передовій українські військовослужбовці. Війна ще не закінчилася, але вона точно закінчиться, й однозначно нашою перемогою. А до того – ми вдячні Вам, нашим закордонним друзям, за моральну підтримку тих, хто боронить Україну. 

Ми боремося за життя, а життя завжди перемагає!🙏🏻
